            p(class="text-gray-700 mb-4")
              | Create Flow, Inc.
              br
              | Effective Date: November 1, 2025

            p(class="text-gray-700 mb-6") Create Flow, Inc. ("Create Flow," "Company," "we," "us," or "our") provides web-based software services to enterprise customers. This Privacy Policy describes how we collect, use, process, store, and disclose information in connection with our services (the "Services"). If you have questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at: contact@create-flow.ai

            h3(class="font-heading text-xl font-bold mb-4 mt-8") 1. Scope
            p(class="text-gray-700 mb-6") This Privacy Policy applies to:
            ul(class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 mb-6")
              li Enterprise customers of Create Flow
              li Authorized users of customer accounts
              li Visitors to our website
              li Individuals whose information is processed through our Services

            p(class="text-gray-700 mb-6") This policy does not apply to third-party services that may integrate with or connect to our Services.

            h3(class="font-heading text-xl font-bold mb-4 mt-8") 2. Information We Collect
            p(class="text-gray-700 mb-4") We may collect and process the following categories of information:

            h4(class="font-semibold mb-2") A. Information Provided Directly
            ul(class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 mb-6")
              li Account registration details (name, email address, company name)
              li Billing and payment information
              li Communications with us
              li Information uploaded or submitted through the Services

            h4(class="font-semibold mb-2") B. Automatically Collected Information
            ul(class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 mb-6")
              li Log data (IP address, browser type, device information)
              li Usage data (features accessed, session duration)
              li Cookies and similar tracking technologies

            h4(class="font-semibold mb-2") C. Customer Data
            p(class="text-gray-700 mb-6") Enterprise customers may upload, transmit, or otherwise provide data to be processed by our Services ("Customer Data"). We process Customer Data solely on behalf of the customer and in accordance with applicable agreements.

            h3(class="font-heading text-xl font-bold mb-4 mt-8") 3. How We Use Information
            p(class="text-gray-700 mb-6") We use information to:
            ul(class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 mb-6")
              li Provide, operate, and maintain the Services
              li Authenticate users and manage accounts
              li Improve functionality and performance
              li Provide customer support
              li Comply with legal obligations
              li Enforce contractual rights

            p(class="text-gray-700 mb-6") We do not sell personal information.

            h3(class="font-heading text-xl font-bold mb-4 mt-8") 4. Data Processing and Third-Party Services
            p(class="text-gray-700 mb-6") We may use third-party service providers to support our operations, including but not limited to:
            ul(class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 mb-6")
              li Cloud hosting providers
              li Infrastructure and data storage providers
              li Analytics services
              li Payment processors
              li Security and monitoring providers

            p(class="text-gray-700 mb-6") These third parties may process information on our behalf. While we select vendors based on reasonable security and reliability standards, third-party providers operate independently and may be subject to their own privacy and security practices. Information processed by third-party providers may be subject to risks inherent in digital transmission, storage, and processing, including unauthorized access, data breaches, or system failures.

            h3(class="font-heading text-xl font-bold mb-4 mt-8") 5. Data Security
            p(class="text-gray-700 mb-6") Create Flow implements commercially reasonable technical and organizational safeguards designed to protect information against unauthorized access, alteration, disclosure, or destruction. However, no method of transmission over the internet or electronic storage system is completely secure. While we make best efforts to protect information using reasonable security measures, we cannot guarantee absolute security.

            p(class="text-gray-700 mb-6") To the maximum extent permitted by applicable law:
            ul(class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 mb-6")
              li Create Flow does not guarantee that data will be free from unauthorized access, loss, or breach.
              li Create Flow shall not be liable for security breaches, data leaks, or unauthorized access that occur despite reasonable safeguards, including incidents affecting third-party service providers.

            h3(class="font-heading text-xl font-bold mb-4 mt-8") 6. Data Retention
            p(class="text-gray-700 mb-6") We retain information:
            ul(class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 mb-6")
              li As long as necessary to provide the Services
              li As required by contractual obligations
              li As necessary to comply with legal requirements
              li As needed to resolve disputes and enforce agreements

            p(class="text-gray-700 mb-6") Customer Data may be deleted upon termination of the applicable agreement, subject to backup retention policies and legal obligations.

            h3(class="font-heading text-xl font-bold mb-4 mt-8") 7. International Data Transfers
            p(class="text-gray-700 mb-6") Information may be processed and stored in jurisdictions outside of your location. By using our Services, you acknowledge that data may be transferred across borders and processed in countries with different data protection laws.

            h3(class="font-heading text-xl font-bold mb-4 mt-8") 8. Confidentiality (Enterprise Customers)
            p(class="text-gray-700 mb-6") We treat Customer Data as confidential and process it solely for the purpose of providing the Services, subject to the applicable Master Services Agreement or enterprise contract.

            h3(class="font-heading text-xl font-bold mb-4 mt-8") 9. Your Rights
            p(class="text-gray-700 mb-6") Depending on applicable law, individuals may have rights to:
            ul(class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 mb-6")
              li Access their personal information
              li Request correction or deletion
              li Restrict or object to processing
              li Request data portability

            p(class="text-gray-700 mb-6") Requests may be submitted to: contact@create-flow.ai

            h3(class="font-heading text-xl font-bold mb-4 mt-8") 10. Incident Response
            p(class="text-gray-700 mb-6") In the event of a confirmed security incident affecting Customer Data, we will notify impacted customers in accordance with contractual obligations and applicable law.

            h3(class="font-heading text-xl font-bold mb-4 mt-8") 11. Changes to This Policy
            p(class="text-gray-700 mb-6") We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Material changes will be posted on our website with an updated effective date.

